**************************************************************************************************************
**************************************************************************************************************
	LISTS	
**************************************************************************************************************
**************************************************************************************************************

*************************************************
Data Lists: used for descriptive statistics
store correct latencies/accuracy data
fill up during runtime
*************************************************

Note: list stores 1 = correct response; 0 = incorrect response for each relevant trial
<list accuracy>
</list>

Note: list stores the latency of correct responses for each relevant trial
<list latencies>
</list>

Note: list stores 1 = correct response; 0 = incorrect response for each relevant pattern trial
<list accuracyP>
</list>

Note: list stores the latency of correct responses for each relevant pattern trial
<list latenciesP>
</list>

Note: list stores 1 = correct response; 0 = incorrect response for each relevant random trial
<list accuracyR>
</list>

Note: list stores the latency of correct responses for each relevant random trial
<list latenciesR>
</list>

Note: stores the median correct latencies in pattern trials from each block
<list medianRTs_P>
</list>

Note: stores the median correct latencies in random trials from each block
<list medianRTs_R>
</list>

Note: stores the proportion corrects of pattern trials from each block
<list propCorrect_P>
</list>

Note: stores the proportion corrects of random trials from each block
<list propCorrect_R>
</list>

**************************************************************************************************************
**************************************************************************************************************
	TRIALS 	
**************************************************************************************************************
**************************************************************************************************************

<trial start>
/ ontrialbegin = [
	text.box1.textBgColor = gray;
	text.box2.textBgColor = gray;		
	text.box3.textBgColor = gray;		
	text.box4.textBgColor = gray;	
]
/ stimulusframes = [1 = box1, box2, box3, box4]

//for touchscreens: present the inactive response buttons
/ validresponse = (parameters.responsekey1, parameters.responsekey2, parameters.responsekey3, parameters.responsekey4)
/ isvalidresponse = [
	return false;
]

/ trialduration = parameters.RSI
/ recorddata = false
</trial>

Note: runs a single random Trial
- resets boxcolor of all boxes to gray before randomly selecting one to present in red
- presents all 4 boxes and waits for response
- terminates with a correct response only
<trial startTrial>
/ ontrialbegin = [
	text.box1.textBgColor = gray;
	text.box2.textBgColor = gray;		
	text.box3.textBgColor = gray;		
	text.box4.textBgColor = gray;	
	values.position = list.randomPosition.nextValue;
	if (values.position == 1) {
		text.box1.textBgColor = red;
	} else if (values.position == 2) {
		text.box2.textBgColor = red;
	} else if (values.position == 3) {
		text.box3.textBgColor = red;
	} else if (values.position == 4) {
		text.box4.textBgColor = red;
	} ;
	
	values.index = 0;
]
/ stimulusframes = [1 = box1, box2, box3, box4]
/ beginresponsetime = 0
/ validresponse = (parameters.responsekey1, parameters.responsekey2, parameters.responsekey3, parameters.responsekey4)
/ iscorrectresponse = [
	return (
	(values.position == 1 && trial.startTrial.responseText == parameters.responsekey1) ||
	(values.position == 2 && trial.startTrial.responseText == parameters.responsekey2) ||
	(values.position == 3 && trial.startTrial.responseText == parameters.responsekey3) ||	
	(values.position == 4 && trial.startTrial.responseText == parameters.responsekey4));
]
/ response = correct
/ posttrialpause = parameters.RSI
/ responsemessage = (parameters.responsekey1, text.box1_Feedback, 0)
/ responsemessage = (parameters.responsekey2, text.box2_Feedback, 0)
/ responsemessage = (parameters.responsekey3, text.box3_Feedback, 0)
/ responsemessage = (parameters.responsekey4, text.box4_Feedback, 0)
</trial>



Note: trial.patternTrial
- resets boxcolor of all boxes to gray 
* selects the next values.position from sequence list based on values.index (values.index increases by 1 for sequential calling)
* presents 3 gray boxes and one red box (at values.position)
* waits for keyboard input
* determines correctness of response (latency measured from onset of red box until correct response is given
* terminates with correct response
* updates summary lists
* calls trial.randomTrial

<trial patternTrial>
/ ontrialbegin = [
	values.countRandomTrials = 0;
	values.countPatternTrials += 1;
	if (values.index == 4){
		values.index = 0;
	}
	values.index += 1;
	if (values.index == 1) {
		values.countSequenceReps += 1;
	}
	
	text.box1.textBgColor = gray;
	text.box2.textBgColor = gray;		
	text.box3.textBgColor = gray;		
	text.box4.textBgColor = gray;
	values.position = list.patternPosition.nextValue;
	if (values.position == 1) {
		text.box1.textBgColor = red;
	} else if (values.position == 2) {
		text.box2.textBgColor = red;
	} else if (values.position == 3) {
		text.box3.textBgColor = red;
	} else if (values.position == 4) {
		text.box4.textBgColor = red;
	}
]
/ stimulusframes = [1 = box1, box2, box3, box4]
/ beginresponsetime = 0
/ validresponse = (parameters.responsekey1, parameters.responsekey2, parameters.responsekey3, parameters.responsekey4)
/ iscorrectresponse = [
	return (
	(values.position == 1 && trial.patternTrial.responseText == parameters.responsekey1) ||
	(values.position == 2 && trial.patternTrial.responseText == parameters.responsekey2) ||
	(values.position == 3 && trial.patternTrial.responseText == parameters.responsekey3) ||	
	(values.position == 4 && trial.patternTrial.responseText == parameters.responsekey4));	
]
/ response = correct
/ ontrialend = [
	
	list.accuracy.insertItem(trial.patternTrial.correct, 1);
	list.accuracyP.insertItem(trial.patternTrial.correct, 1);
	list.latencies.insertItem(trial.patternTrial.latency, 1);
	list.latenciesP.insertItem(trial.patternTrial.latency, 1);

]
/ posttrialpause = parameters.RSI
/ branch = [
	if (parameters.lag > 1){
		return trial.randomTrial;		
	} else {
		if (values.countSequenceReps == parameters.maxPatternRepetitions){
			values.stop == 1;
		}
		return trial.patternTrial;
	}

]
/ responsemessage = (parameters.responsekey1, text.box1_Feedback, 0)
/ responsemessage = (parameters.responsekey2, text.box2_Feedback, 0)
/ responsemessage = (parameters.responsekey3, text.box3_Feedback, 0)
/ responsemessage = (parameters.responsekey4, text.box4_Feedback, 0)
</trial>

Note: trial.randomTrial
* resets boxcolor of all boxes to gray before randomly selecting one to present in red
* presents 3 gray boxes and one red box (at values.position)
* waits for keyboard input
* determines correctness of response (latency measured from onset of red box until correct response is given
* terminates with correct response
* updates summary lists
* depending on number of random trials presented AND parameters.lag set, calls another
trial.randomTrial
<trial randomTrial>
/ ontrialbegin = [

	values.countRandomTrials += 1;
	text.box1.textBgColor = gray;
	text.box2.textBgColor = gray;		
	text.box3.textBgColor = gray;		
	text.box4.textBgColor = gray;	
	values.position = list.randomPosition.nextValue;
	if (values.position == 1) {
		text.box1.textBgColor = red;
	} else if (values.position == 2) {
		text.box2.textBgColor = red;
	} else if (values.position == 3) {
		text.box3.textBgColor = red;
	} else if (values.position == 4) {
		text.box4.textBgColor = red;
	} ;
]
/ stimulusframes = [1 = box1, box2, box3, box4]
/ beginresponsetime = 0
/ validresponse = (parameters.responsekey1, parameters.responsekey2, parameters.responsekey3, parameters.responsekey4)
/ iscorrectresponse = [
	return (
	(values.position == 1 && trial.randomTrial.responseText == parameters.responsekey1) ||
	(values.position == 2 && trial.randomTrial.responseText == parameters.responsekey2) ||
	(values.position == 3 && trial.randomTrial.responseText == parameters.responsekey3) ||	
	(values.position == 4 && trial.randomTrial.responseText == parameters.responsekey4));
]
/ ontrialend = [
	list.accuracy.insertItem(trial.randomTrial.correct, 1);
	list.accuracyR.insertItem(trial.randomTrial.correct, 1);
	list.latencies.insertItem(trial.randomTrial.latency, 1);
	list.latenciesR.insertItem(trial.randomTrial.latency, 1);
]
/ response = correct
/ branch = [
	if (values.countRandomTrials < parameters.lag-1){
		return trial.randomTrial;
	} else {
		if (values.countSequenceReps == parameters.maxPatternRepetitions && values.index == 4){
			values.stop = 1;			
		}
		return trial.patternTrial;
	}
]
/ posttrialpause = parameters.RSI
/ responsemessage = (parameters.responsekey1, text.box1_Feedback, 0)
/ responsemessage = (parameters.responsekey2, text.box2_Feedback, 0)
/ responsemessage = (parameters.responsekey3, text.box3_Feedback, 0)
/ responsemessage = (parameters.responsekey4, text.box4_Feedback, 0)
</trial>


**************************************************************************************************************
**************************************************************************************************************
	BLOCKS
**************************************************************************************************************
**************************************************************************************************************

<block intro>
/ trials = [1 = instructions]
</block>


Note: block.ASRT
* runs 40 pattern trials and as many random Trials in between as dictated by parameters.lag
* presents a break trial at the end (unless it's the last block run)
* calls another block.ASRT unless the specified number of ASRT has been run
<block ASRT>
/ stop = [
	values.stop == 1;
]
/ onblockbegin = [
	values.countTestBlocks += 1;
	values.countPatternTrials = 0;
	values.countRandomTrials = 0;
	values.countSequenceReps = 0;
	values.stop = 0;
	
	list.accuracyP.reset();
	list.accuracyR.reset();
	list.latenciesP.reset();
	list.latenciesR.reset();
	
	if (mod(values.countTestBlocks, 2) != 0){
		list.accuracy.reset();
		list.latencies.reset();
	}
	
	if (values.countTestBlocks == parameters.nrBlocks){
		values.skipbreak == 1;
	}
]
/trials = [
	1 = getReady;
	2 = start;
	3-12 = startTrial;
	13 = patternTrial;
]
/ onblockend = [
	list.propCorrect_P.insertItem(list.accuracyP.mean, 1);
	list.medianRTs_P.insertItem(list.latenciesP.median, 1);
	list.propCorrect_R.insertItem(list.accuracyR.mean, 1);
	list.medianRTs_R.insertItem(list.latenciesR.median, 1);

	if (values.countTestBlocks == 1){
		values.ACC1_P = list.accuracyP.mean;
		values.RT1_P = list.latenciesP.median;
		values.ACC1_R = list.accuracyR.mean;
		values.RT1_R = list.latenciesR.median;		
	} else if (values.countTestBlocks == 2){
		values.ACC2_P = list.accuracyP.mean;
		values.RT2_P = list.latenciesP.median;
		values.ACC2_R = list.accuracyR.mean;
		values.RT2_R = list.latenciesR.median;		
	} else if (values.countTestBlocks == 3){
		values.ACC3_P = list.accuracyP.mean;
		values.RT3_P = list.latenciesP.median;
		values.ACC3_R = list.accuracyR.mean;
		values.RT3_R = list.latenciesR.median;		
	} else if (values.countTestBlocks == 4){
		values.ACC4_P = list.accuracyP.mean;
		values.RT4_P = list.latenciesP.median;
		values.ACC4_R = list.accuracyR.mean;
		values.RT4_R = list.latenciesR.median;		
	} else if (values.countTestBlocks == 5){
		values.ACC5_P = list.accuracyP.mean;
		values.RT5_P = list.latenciesP.median;
		values.ACC5_R = list.accuracyR.mean;
		values.RT5_R = list.latenciesR.median;		
	} else if (values.countTestBlocks == 6){
		values.ACC6_P = list.accuracyP.mean;
		values.RT6_P = list.latenciesP.median;
		values.ACC6_R = list.accuracyR.mean;
		values.RT6_R = list.latenciesR.median;		
	} else if (values.countTestBlocks == 7){
		values.ACC7_P = list.accuracyP.mean;
		values.RT7_P = list.latenciesP.median;
		values.ACC7_R = list.accuracyR.mean;
		values.RT7_R = list.latenciesR.median;		
	} else if (values.countTestBlocks == 8){
		values.ACC8_P = list.accuracyP.mean;
		values.RT8_P = list.latenciesP.median;
		values.ACC8_R = list.accuracyR.mean;
		values.RT8_R = list.latenciesR.median;		
	} else if (values.countTestBlocks == 9){
		values.ACC9_P = list.accuracyP.mean;
		values.RT9_P = list.latenciesP.median;
		values.ACC9_R = list.accuracyR.mean;
		values.RT9_R = list.latenciesR.median;		
	} else if (values.countTestBlocks == 10){
		values.ACC10_P = list.accuracyP.mean;
		values.RT10_P = list.latenciesP.median;
		values.ACC10_R = list.accuracyR.mean;
		values.RT10_R = list.latenciesR.median;		
	} else if (values.countTestBlocks == 11){
		values.ACC11_P = list.accuracyP.mean;
		values.RT11_P = list.latenciesP.median;
		values.ACC11_R = list.accuracyR.mean;
		values.RT11_R = list.latenciesR.median;		
	} else if (values.countTestBlocks == 12){
		values.ACC12_P = list.accuracyP.mean;
		values.RT12_P = list.latenciesP.median;
		values.ACC12_R = list.accuracyR.mean;
		values.RT12_R = list.latenciesR.median;		
	} else if (values.countTestBlocks == 13){
		values.ACC13_P = list.accuracyP.mean;
		values.RT13_P = list.latenciesP.median;
		values.ACC13_R = list.accuracyR.mean;
		values.RT13_R = list.latenciesR.median;		
	} else if (values.countTestBlocks == 14){
		values.ACC14_P = list.accuracyP.mean;
		values.RT14_P = list.latenciesP.median;
		values.ACC14_R = list.accuracyR.mean;
		values.RT14_R = list.latenciesR.median;		
	} else if (values.countTestBlocks == 15){
		values.ACC15_P = list.accuracyP.mean;
		values.RT15_P = list.latenciesP.median;
		values.ACC15_R = list.accuracyR.mean;
		values.RT15_R = list.latenciesR.median;		
	} else if (values.countTestBlocks == 16){
		values.ACC16_P = list.accuracyP.mean;
		values.RT16_P = list.latenciesP.median;
		values.ACC16_R = list.accuracyR.mean;
		values.RT16_R = list.latenciesR.median;		
	} else if (values.countTestBlocks == 17){
		values.ACC17_P = list.accuracyP.mean;
		values.RT17_P = list.latenciesP.median;
		values.ACC17_R = list.accuracyR.mean;
		values.RT17_R = list.latenciesR.median;		
	} else if (values.countTestBlocks == 18){
		values.ACC18_P = list.accuracyP.mean;
		values.RT18_P = list.latenciesP.median;
		values.ACC18_R = list.accuracyR.mean;
		values.RT18_R = list.latenciesR.median;		
	} else if (values.countTestBlocks == 19){
		values.ACC19_P = list.accuracyP.mean;
		values.RT19_P = list.latenciesP.median;
		values.ACC19_R = list.accuracyR.mean;
		values.RT19_R = list.latenciesR.median;		
	} else if (values.countTestBlocks == 20){
		values.ACC20_P = list.accuracyP.mean;
		values.RT20_P = list.latenciesP.median;
		values.ACC20_R = list.accuracyR.mean;
		values.RT20_R = list.latenciesR.median;		
	}  else if (values.countTestBlocks == 21){
		values.ACC21_P = list.accuracyP.mean;
		values.RT21_P = list.latenciesP.median;
		values.ACC21_R = list.accuracyR.mean;
		values.RT21_R = list.latenciesR.median;		
	}
]
/ branch = [
	return block.break;
]
</block>


<block break>
/ trials = [1 = break]
/ branch = [
	if (values.countTestBlocks  < parameters.nrBlocks){
		return block.ASRT;		
	}
]
</block>

<block finish>
/ trials = [
	1 = finish;
]
</block>

